Suggests: openssh-server
Description: QUIC-based SSH proxy server and client
 quicssh is a QUIC proxy that allows to use QUIC to connect to an SSH server
 without needing to patch the client or the server.
 .
 This fork includes:
  - Session persistence across network changes (laptop sleep, VPN reconnect)
  - Network-aware reconnection with platform-specific monitoring
  - Updated dependencies with latest security patches
  - Optimized data transfer throughput for bulk operations (SCP, SFTP)
  - Configurable idle timeout for flaky connections
  - TLS certificate verification support and reloading certs at runtime
  - NAT punching support
  - Custom SSH daemon address
 .
 The package includes a systemd service for running quicssh server as a daemon
 with proper security hardening and automatic certificate management.
